A Thermal Forcing System is a specialized setup or device that generates, controls, and transfers heat energy within a dedicated environment or between interconnected systems. These systems are widely employed in scientific research laboratories, industrial manufacturing processes, and HVAC (heating, ventilation, and air‑conditioning) applications where precise thermal regulation is critical for product quality and energy efficiency.
